classes.name: FractalDimensionCalculator
classes.docstring: Calculates various fractal dimensions for spatial data.

methods.name: __init__
methods.docstring:
Initialize the fractal dimension calculator.

Args:
    method: Method to use for fractal dimension calculation
           Options: "box_counting", "correlation", "information", "hausdorff"

methods.name: calculate
methods.docstring:
Calculate the fractal dimension of the provided coordinates.

Args:
    coordinates: Array of coordinates in any dimension
    
Returns:
    Fractal dimension value

classes.name: MultifractalSpectrumAnalyzer
classes.docstring: Analyzes the multifractal spectrum of spatial data.

methods.name: __init__
methods.docstring:
Initialize the multifractal spectrum analyzer.

Args:
    q_values: Range of q values for multifractal analysis (default: -5 to 5)
    scales: Scales at which to compute the analysis (default: logspace from 0.001 to 1)

methods.name: analyze
methods.docstring:
Compute the multifractal spectrum of the provided coordinates.

Args:
    coordinates: Array of coordinates in any dimension
    
Returns:
    Dictionary containing multifractal spectrum information:
        - alpha: Singularity strengths
        - f_alpha: Multifractal spectrum
        - q: Moment orders
        - tau: Mass exponents
        - D_q: Generalized dimensions

classes.name: DimensionalResonanceDetector
classes.docstring: Detects resonance patterns in fractal dimensions across different spatial configurations.

methods.name: __init__
methods.docstring:
Initialize the dimensional resonance detector.

Args:
    resonance_threshold: Maximum difference to consider dimensions as resonating
    cluster_eps: DBSCAN clustering parameter
    min_cluster_size: Minimum points to form a cluster

methods.name: detect_resonances
methods.docstring:
Detect dimensional resonances across multiple spatial configurations.

Args:
    configurations: List of coordinate arrays representing different spatial configs
    
Returns:
    Dictionary containing resonance information:
        - resonance_clusters: Groups of configurations with similar fractal properties
        - resonance_strength: Measure of resonance intensity
        - resonance_patterns: Specific dimensional patterns detected
        - resonance_graph: NetworkX graph of resonance relationships

methods.name: generate_resonance_fingerprint
methods.docstring:
Generate a unique fractal fingerprint for a spatial configuration.

Args:
    config: Coordinate array representing a spatial configuration
    
Returns:
    Hexadecimal fingerprint string

classes.name: FractalDimensionResonanceMapping
classes.docstring: Main class for Fractal Dimension Resonance Mapping (FDRM).

methods.name: analyze_negative_space
methods.docstring:
Analyze the fractal properties of a negative space configuration.

Args:
    coordinates: Array of coordinates representing the negative space
    
Returns:
    Dictionary of fractal analysis results

methods.name: detect_resonances
methods.docstring:
Detect dimensional resonances across multiple spatial configurations.

Args:
    configurations: List of coordinate arrays
    
Returns:
    Resonance detection results

methods.name: compress_negative_space
methods.docstring:
Compress negative space data using fractal properties.

Args:
    coordinates: Array of coordinates representing the negative space
    
Returns:
    Dictionary with compressed representation and metadata
